We identified crystal structures with predicted $E_{\mathrm{v}}$ in the target range and performed structural optimization again under tighter conditions. The accurate $E_{\mathrm{v}}$ of the remaining crystal structures were computed from their supercells. Finally, we obtained 14 newly constructed crystal structures that have both the predicted and computed $E_{\mathrm{v}}$.

